## Tasks

### Task 1: Migrate hardcoded colors to semantic tokens

<read_first>
- frontend/src/index.css (source of truth for all design tokens and their oklch/sRGB values)
- frontend/src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx (reference implementation — correctly uses design tokens)
- frontend/src/pages/auth/LoginPage.tsx (reference implementation — correctly uses design tokens)
</read_first>

<action>
For each of the 30 files listed in `files_modified`, search for and replace hardcoded color patterns using these rules from UI-SPEC.md:

| Hardcoded Pattern | Semantic Token |
|-------------------|---------------|
| `text-slate-900`, `text-slate-950`, `text-gray-900` | `text-foreground` |
| `text-slate-600`, `text-slate-500`, `text-gray-600`, `text-gray-500` | `text-muted-foreground` |
| `text-slate-400`, `text-slate-300`, `text-gray-400` | `text-muted-foreground` |
| `text-white` (as primary text) | `text-foreground` |
| `dark:text-white` | remove `dark:` variant (token handles it) |
| `bg-white` (as card/panel bg) | `bg-card` |
| `dark:bg-slate-950`, `dark:bg-slate-900` | remove `dark:` variant (token handles it) |
| `bg-slate-50`, `bg-gray-50` | `bg-muted` |
| `bg-slate-100`, `bg-gray-100` | `bg-secondary` |
| `border-slate-200`, `border-gray-200` | `border-border` |
| `dark:border-slate-800`, `dark:border-slate-700` | remove `dark:` variant (token handles it) |
| `rounded-2xl`, `rounded-[28px]` | `rounded-xl` or `rounded-lg` |
| `dark:bg-slate-800` | `dark:bg-card` or remove if token covers it |
| `dark:text-slate-300`, `dark:text-slate-400` | remove `dark:` variant (token handles it) |

For each file:
1. Read the full file
2. Identify all hardcoded color patterns
3. Replace with semantic tokens per the table above
4. Verify the replacement makes visual sense (e.g., `bg-white` on a card surface → `bg-card`, not `bg-background`)

**Important:** Do NOT change functional color classes like `bg-green-100`, `text-red-700`, `bg-blue-100` — these are semantic status colors, not theme-dependent colors. Only replace `slate-*`, `gray-*`, and `white` patterns.
</action>

